                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>Although Marvin Bagley III and R.J. Barrett never got a chance to team up on the court in Durham, the pair of former Blue Devil freshman standouts now have another shared connection: their shoe deal.</p>
<p>Despite being the last of his former Duke teammates to decide on a shoe company, Barrett made waves Wednesday when it was announced that he would sign a contract with Puma. This signing doesn’t come as a surprise to those closely following Barrett, as he not only wore a Puma jacket in the video of him receiving his NBA 2K ratings, but he also sported Puma kicks in his rookie photo shoot for the Knicks a couple weeks ago.&nbsp;</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
