<p>Puma announced this multi-year deal with Barrett with a mural outside a Manhattan Puma store.&nbsp;</p>
<div class="embed"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">OFFICIAL: RJ Barrett has signed a multi-year shoe deal with PUMA.<br><br>More to come live from New York on 31st Street at 4:30 PM... <a href="https://t.co/0INe0BPolV">pic.twitter.com/0INe0BPolV</a></p>&mdash; Nick DePaula (@NickDePaula) <a href="https://twitter.com/NickDePaula/status/1166767699378266113?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">August 28, 2019</a></blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>The news comes just a few weeks after Barrett’s college teammates Cam Reddish and Zion Williamson announced shoe deals of their own with Nike and Jordan respectively. With this signing, Puma continues to make big moves in the NBA shoe game, as they signed Terry Rozier, DeAndre Ayton and Bagley III as feature athletes last year.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Barrett will also be one of Puma’s marketable faces, as the third overall pick in the 2019 NBA draft will have a lot of rookie responsibilities in Madison Square Garden this upcoming season as a New York Knick.&nbsp;</p>

